      serialVersionUID:
      -5227967083951048166L

      • Serialized Fields

        • receiver

          TransactionFee.Subject receiver

        • toFixedMember

          Member toFixedMember

        • h

          java.math.BigDecimal h
          the highest (start) value of the A-rate based fast conversion tax F; null if A-rate is disabled. This is the value of the fast conversion tax if conversion would take place immediately after creation.

        • aFIsZero

          java.math.BigDecimal aFIsZero
          the time in days after which the fast conversion tax F reaches zero. The fast conversion tax F is A-rate based.

        • f1

          java.math.BigDecimal f1
          value of the fast conversion tax F at day 1.

        • fInfinite

          java.math.BigDecimal fInfinite
          the value of the horizontal asymptote to which the fast conversion tax F diminishes.

        • fMinimal

          java.math.BigDecimal fMinimal
          the minimal value of the fast conversion tax F. If a calculated tax is smaller than fMinimal, the fast conversion tax F will be set to fMinimal. Usually, this is 0 (zero).

        • gFIsZero

          java.math.BigDecimal gFIsZero
          the percentage of the total guarantee period after which the fast conversion tax F reaches 0. This is only used in case of a combined A-rate and D-rate, which are both used to determine a diminishing fast conversion tax F.

  • Package nl.strohalm.cyclos.services.stats

    • Class nl.strohalm.cyclos.services.stats.StatisticalResultDTO extends DataObject implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      7243923567624382393L

      • Serialized Fields

        • rows

          int rows
          the number of rows

        • columns

          int columns
          the number of columns

        • rowKeys

          StatisticalResultDTO.ResourceKey[] rowKeys
          the keys for the row headers of the table. The real headers must be fetched from the language resource bundle with these keys.

        • rowHeaders

          java.lang.String[] rowHeaders
          the real strings for the row headers. In some cases, these strings are NOT fetched from the language resource bundle, for example in case of a payment filter name. In such a case, the actual name is stored in this field.

        • columnKeys

          java.lang.String[] columnKeys
          the keys for the column headers of the table. The real headers are fetched from the language resource bundle with these keys.

        • columnHeaders

          java.lang.String[] columnHeaders
          the headers above the table columns; these are also the seriesNames of the graph. This is used in case the strings are not fetched from the resource bundles, for example with strings like "2006" or "%".

        • columnSubHeaders

          java.lang.String[] columnSubHeaders
          the subheaders above the table columns; usually these are used to indicate the units in the column.

        • tableCells

          java.lang.Number[][] tableCells
          The data for the table; can only be set via the constructor

        • categoryCount

          java.lang.Integer categoryCount
          The number of categories in the graph. Categories are set on the x-axis; usually, this correspondents to the rows in the table, or in some exceptional cases (when dontSwitchXY == true It can have the following values:
          • null: all categories in the table will be rendered in the graph.
          • value > number of table categories: ignored, treated as if it were null.
          • value < number of table categories: only this amount of categories is shown in the table, starting from the first category. So the last or the last few categories which are in the table will not be shown in the graph.

          So set this field only if there are categories you want to show in the table but exclude from the graph.

        • seriesCount

          java.lang.Integer seriesCount
          The number of series in the graph. Series are set in the legend of the graph; usually, this correspondents to the columns in the table, or in some exceptional cases (when dontSwitchXY == true It can have the following values:
          • null: all series in the table will be rendered in the graph.
          • value > number of table series: ignored, treated as if it were null.
          • value < number of table series: only this amount of series is shown in the table, starting from the first serie. So the last or the last few series which are in the table will not be shown in the graph.

          So set this field only if there are series you want to show in the table but exclude from the graph.

        • baseKey

          java.lang.String baseKey
          this is the base key for the language resource files.
          Language Strings are being taken from this resource file by this base key.
          The basekey is used for the following, so all of these must be provided in the language resource bundle:
          • plain basekey is used for the graph title
          • basekey.title is used as the title of the surrounding window
          • basekey.yAxis is used as the title along the y-axis of the graph
          • basekey.xAxis is used as the title along the x-axis of the graph
          • basekey.rowN is used as the name of the Nth data row in the table
          • basekey.rowN.short is used as a shorter version of this name, to appear at the x-Axis below the Nth category in the graph. Note that this string must be as short as possible to fit in the graph.
          • Helpfile: all the dots (.) are deleted from the basekey, the elements between the dots are capitalized for their first letter, and a .jsp is appended. This needs to be provided as a help file.

        • subTitle

          java.lang.String subTitle
          subtitle above the graph or above the leftmost column in the table

        • scaleFactorX

          java.lang.String scaleFactorX
          the scalefactor for the x-axis. This is usually not used, but it may contains Strings like "(x 1000)".

        • graphType

          StatisticalResultDTO.GraphType graphType
          the type of the graph, can be one of BAR, LINE, PIE or NONE

        • multiGraph

          StatisticalResultDTO.MultiGraph multiGraph
          indicates if the chart is a combined chart. If so, for each series (column) OR for each category (table row) a separate graph is created. The graphs are tiled in vertical direction, while there is one combined x-axis. If none (the default), all series and categories are shown in one single graph, having both x-axis and y-axis in common. The table just shows all the series and categories, independant of the value of this field. So this field only effects the presentation of the graph, not of the table.

        • showTable

          boolean showTable
          true if the table must NOT be shown. This is true in case of histograms.

        • dontSwitchXY

          boolean dontSwitchXY
          For most graphs, x and y of the table need to be switched in order to display the graph correctly.
          In special cases, this does NOT need to be switched. In such a case, set dontSwitchXY to true.

        • filtersUsed

          java.util.List<E> filtersUsed
          the list with used filters, to be displayed in the "Filters used" box below each graph or table.

        • yAxisUnits

          java.lang.String yAxisUnits
          a String representing the units to be displayed along the y axis of a graph.

        • xAxisUnits

          java.lang.String xAxisUnits
          a String representing the units to be displayed along the x axis of a graph.

        • helpFile

          java.lang.String helpFile
          a String used to set the help file. The default is "statistics". Only use in case this is another file than statistics.

        • domainMarkers

          org.jfree.chart.plot.Marker[] domainMarkers
          an array of Markers. Markers are horizontal or vertical lines to draw through the graph to mark a special result value or domain value. In this case, these are the domain markers (= vertical lines), but a future version may also include a special field for range markers (= horizontal lines). Markers should be set to the jsp with the following construct: 
                <cewolf:chartpostprocessor id="chartPostProcessorImpl" >
          <cewolf:param name="domainMarkers" value="${dataTable.domainMarkers}" />
      </cewolf:chartpostprocessor>
          For each Marker in the array, you MUST set the place where the marker is to be drawn in the graph. In case of Category plots, this is the label which is placed on the x-axis for which you want to put the vertical line in the graph.
          Optionally, you can set a color (setPaint) and a label (setLabel) to the Marker. The label is a string literal; if you want to put a language string in this label, you must set the keys for the marker on the service, and read these and replace them on the action. See for example paymentService.getSimulateConversionGraph and SimulateConversionAction.

          • javax.net.ssl.trustStorePassword (the keystore password to open the keystore)

        • readTimeout

          long readTimeout
          Set the read timeout value in milliseconds. A timeout of zero is interpreted as an infinite timeout Defaults to 60000 ms

        • connectionTimeout

          long connectionTimeout
          Set the connection timeout value in milliseconds. A timeout of zero is interpreted as an infinite timeout Defaults to 60000 ms
